parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering assist can cause the steering wheel to become stiff or difficult to turn, making it challenging to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The power steering assist warning light is illuminated
the steering wheel becomes stiff or difficult to turn
the vehicle becomes hard to steer
the power steering assist fails while driving
the steering wheel seizes or locks up
the vehicle becomes unsafe to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause fires, loss of power steering, and failure of essential systems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Burning electrical odor
flames surrounding the front of the vehicle
loss of power steering
inability to restart the vehicle
dashboard lights flashing
and loss of instrument panel information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the door sensor can cause the car alarm to go off, making it difficult to lock the car, and potentially leading to theft or damage.
symptoms: The door sensor indicates that the door is open when it is not
and the car alarm goes off repeatedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially harm to occupants or others.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
losing total control
and may stop suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the touch screen can cause inconvenience and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The touch screen goes blank
and the driver is unable to operate associated systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Advance Trac and Electrical System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Advance Trac and electrical system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially harm to occupants or others.
symptoms: The Advance Trac indicator comes on
along with control issues in rain and snow
brake lights not shutting off
cruise control not operating
and ignition system failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The multiple failures of the electrical system can cause inconvenience, distraction, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The A/C shuts down
control panel instruments surge forward
the car dies
the A/C turns on by itself
and all codes are reset
making it difficult to diagnose the problem.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the vehicle to stall or go into limp mode, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or dies while driving
the vehicle goes into limp mode
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle experiences jerky motion
the vehicle slows down suddenly
the red wrench light comes on.
